 for column_width in WIDTH_OPTIONS:\r\n        table = Table(show_lines=True, width=table_width)\r\n        table.add_column(\"Column\", no_wrap=True, width=column_width)\r\n        table.add_row(\"Short\")\r\n        table.add_row(\"Width 10!\")\r\n        table.add_row(\"Very long string that exceeds 10 characters in length\")\r\n        console.print(f\"Table width: {table_width}, Column width: {column_width}\", table)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Test result\r\n```\r\nTable width: None, Column width: None\r\n┏━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┓\r\n┃ Column                                                ┃\r\n┡━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┩\r\n│ Short                                                 │\r\n├───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\r\n│ Width 10!                                             │\r\n├───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\r\n│ Very long string that exceeds 10 characters in length │\r\n└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\r\nTable width: None, Column width: 10\r\n┏━━━━━━━━━━━━┓\r\n┃ Column     ┃\r\n┡━━━━━━━━━━━━┩\r\n│ Short      │\r\n├────────────┤\r\n│ Width 10!  │\r\n├────────────┤\r\n│ Very long… │\r\n└────────────┘\r\nTable width: None, Column width: 0\r\n┏━━┓\r\n┃  ┃\r\n┡━━┩\r\n│  │\r\n├──┤\r\n│  │\r\n├──┤\r\n│  │\r\n└──┘\r\nTable width: 10, Column width: None\r\n┏━━━━━━━━┓\r\n┃ Column ┃\r\n┡━━━━━━━━┩\r\n│ Short  │\r\n├────────┤\r\n│ Width… │\r\n├────────┤\r\n│ Very … │\r\n└────────┘\r\nTable width: 10, Column width: 10\r\n┏━━━━━━━━━━━━┓\r\n┃ Column     ┃\r\n┡━━━━━━━━━━━━┩\r\n│ Short      │\r\n├────────────┤\r\n│ Width 10!  │\r\n├────────────┤\r\n│ Very long… │\r\n└────────────┘\r\nTable width: 10, Column width: 0\r\n┏━━━━━━━━┓\r\n┃ Column ┃\r\n┡━━━━━━━━┩\r\n│ Short  │\r\n├────────┤\r\n│ Width… │\r\n├────────┤\r\n│ Very … │\r\n└────────┘\r\nTable width: 0, Column width: None\r\n┏━┓\r\n┃ ┃\r\n┡━┩\r\n│ │\r\n├─┤\r\n│ │\r\n├─┤\r\n│ │\r\n└─┘\r\nTable width: 0, Column width: 10\r\n┏━┓\r\n┃ ┃\r\n┡━┩\r\n│ │\r\n├─┤\r\n│ │\r\n├─┤\r\n│ │\r\n└─┘\r\nTable width: 0, Column width: 0\r\n┏━┓\r\n┃ ┃\r\n┡━┩\r\n│ │\r\n├─┤\r\n│ │\r\n├─┤\r\n│ │\r\n└─┘\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Conclusions\r\n\r\n* The \"width\" parameter is definitely not a minimum as the `add_column` docstring states.\r\n* The total width can exceed the table width if both are specified and greater than zero?","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/709568958","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/388#issuecomment-709568958","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/388","id":709568958,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDcwOTU2ODk1OA==","user":{"login":"willmcgugan","id":554369,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU1NDM2OQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/554369?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-10-15T20:20:40Z","updated_at":"2020-10-15T20:20:40Z","author_association":"OWNER","body":"The width on the column isn't a minimum, the docs are in error and I'll fix.\r\n\r\n@stolarczyk I'd consider implementing a minimum width, but I'd like to hear your use-case first. table.py is a complicated beast and I don't want to add anything without good reason. If you really want it now, you could pad your header with spaces to reach your minimum.\r\n\r\n@Edward-Knight Rich will shrink columns as a last resort if they don't fit within the table width. But it generally tries very hard to do what the developer asks for.","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/709572341","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/388#issuecomment-709572341","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/388","id":709572341,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDcwOTU3MjM0MQ==","user":{"login":"stolarczyk","id":22797900,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyNzk3OTAw","avatar_url":"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/22797900?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/stolarczyk","html_url":"https://github.com/stolarczyk","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stolarczyk/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stolarczyk/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stolarczyk/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stolarczyk/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stolarczyk/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stolarczyk/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stolarczyk/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stolarczyk/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stolarczyk/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-10-15T20:28:07Z","updated_at":"2020-10-15T20:28:53Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"@Edward-Knight, thanks for this thorough presentation. It seems like none of the with combinations suit my needs, though.\r\n\r\n@willmcgugan, for use case presentation can you take a look at the issue that references this one? Linked right below my initial comment. Let me know if it doesn't